						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1312 (= 1390 A.D.)</hi></p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Records the gift of 30 cows and a perpetual lamp by Aṇṇappa-Uḍaiyar-Chauṇḍappa, son of Viṭṭhapa of the Vatsa-gōtra. The Śaka year is expressed by the chronogram <hi rend="bold">Rājyalōkē (1312)</hi> and the details, <hi rend="bold">Pramōda. Kārttika, Utthānadvādaśī</hi> correspond to <hi rend="bold">1390 A.D., October 21.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
